<p>Ukraine’s government has declared a state of emergency in the energy sector after sustained Russian drone and missile attacks damaged power and heating infrastructure during a deep winter cold spell. Kyiv and surrounding areas have faced widespread outages, leaving residents coping with freezing conditions as crews work to stabilize the system. President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said the emergency step aims to speed repairs and secure additional support, including measures to expand backup supply options.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/qHrxFta1XvvgyYOpbD9urB5KYmhlZ-4ZW8Q9fYMikvYQ48ijSCgzZFQ35KvvrqCdFfuCFUoNX40QGC7iRczvyMVJ8ukVzB5nmIWnq_QpRLScjUqKF2CC3x4oNbkoZ5lNDe6zTcpBAXHj0gl0t8dqoio2A0TkuaqZKQsFJNVLxoRyi5OnXoYTcEhwoGnQ7lkIV2go5dTDqU8qbj1bucp9l6_FH4rH9vgAkLHDwLfa8q9_3PeAoPC6mi0S7sj3LX2Yi_fhD6Ca-6e0stowFw' alt='Electricians carry out emergency repairs on a power pole after a transformer burned out due to a voltage surge caused by regular Russian air attacks on the country&#x27;s energy infrastructure in Kyiv region, Ukraine, Wednesday, Jan. 14, 2026. (AP Photo/Dan Bashakov)' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Kyiv power rationing: In Kyiv, emergency repairs have enabled limited scheduled electricity availability—reported as about four hours per day—while crews keep working through the cold.</li><li>Backup rules eased: Zelenskyy said he instructed officials to deregulate elements of backup energy supply as authorities try to keep heat and light on during the winter disruption.</li><li>Allies urged faster: Zelenskyy also ordered a push to scale up efforts to obtain additional assistance from partners as infrastructure comes under repeated attack.</li><li>Trump peace comment: US President Donald Trump said Ukraine is “less ready” than Russia’s president to make a peace deal, a remark noted alongside news of the emergency declaration.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Ukrainian government (President Volodymyr Zelenskyy): Zelenskyy frames the energy emergency as a tool to accelerate recovery—seeking more allied support and loosening rules to expand backup power options as winter outages persist. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2026/01/15/zelensky-to-declare-state-of-emergency-in-ukraine-s-energy-sector_6749438_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>Ukraine’s leadership (Zelenskyy): Zelenskyy describes the situation as an energy emergency driven by Russian strikes, with temperatures dropping sharply and urgent work needed to restore heat and electricity. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/15/russian-attacks-cause-energy-emergency-in-freezing-ukraine-says-zelenskyy'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>United States (President Donald Trump): President Trump says Ukraine appears “less ready” than Russia’s leader to reach a peace deal, as the energy crisis continues. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cq6vm677z76o'>BBC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/15/russian-attacks-cause-energy-emergency-in-freezing-ukraine-says-zelenskyy'>Russian attacks cause energy emergency in freezing Ukraine, says Zelenskyy</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/ukraines-zelenskiy-to-declare-energy-emergency-after-russian-attacks'>Ukraine’s Zelensky to declare energy emergency to tackle aftermath of Russian attacks</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cq6vm677z76o'>Zelensky declares energy emergency as biting cold persists</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-russia-ukraine-war-kyiv-power-outage-weather-putin-zelensky/'>Russian attacks knock out power in Kyiv, leaving Ukrainians at the mercy of freezing weather</a> - theglobeandmail.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2026/01/15/zelensky-to-declare-state-of-emergency-in-ukraine-s-energy-sector_6749438_4.html'>Zelensky to declare &#x27;state of emergency&#x27; in Ukra